[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scotland's jobless total rises again

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Unemployment in Scotland rose by 9,000 between December and February and now stands at 167,000, according to official statistics.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It was the second rise in a row, following an increase of 6,000 in the previous set of figures.
The unemployment rate in Scotland is now 6%, compared with 5.6% for the UK as a whole.
Employment was up by 3,000 to reach 2,615,000, according to the Office for National Statistics.
